<statement>
<p>Solve this system of equations using elimination.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{x}-{6}{y}={46}</m> </p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle-{4}{x}+{2}{y}=-{50}</m></p>
<p><fillin characters="8" /></p>

</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li><m>\displaystyle{\left({8},-{9}\right)}</m></li></ul></p><p>We chose (for no special reason) to use the first equation to eliminate x from the second equation.</p>
<p>To eliminate we need the scaled version of equation one to have a coefficient of --4. So we scale by <m>\displaystyle--\frac{{4}}{{-{{1}}}}</m>.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-\frac{{-{4}}}{{-{{1}}}}{\left(-{1}{x}+-{6}{y}\right)}=-\frac{{-{4}}}{{-{{1}}}}{\left({46}\right)}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{\left(-{4}\right)}{x}+{24}{y}=-{184}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{4}{x}+{2}{y}=-{50}</m></p>
<p>Adding these two equations gives us</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{26}{y}=-{234}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{y}=-\frac{{234}}{{26}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{y}=-{9}</m></p>
<p>Finally we can substitute this y value into the first equation to solve for x.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{1}{x}+-{6}{\left(-{9}\right)}={46}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{1}{x}+{\left({54}\right)}={46}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{1}{x}={46}-{\left({54}\right)}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{1}{x}=-{8}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=-\frac{{8}}{{-{{1}}}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}={8}</m></p>
<p>Thus the answer is <m>\displaystyle{\left({8},-{9}\right)}</m>.</p>

</solution>
</myopenmath>

